Easily distinguished from known congeners by armature of male chelicerae (
Fig. 329
; pair of large frontal processes, each with subdistal ventral branch) and epigynum with pair of large pointed posterior processes (
Figs 334–337
); also by two distinctive elements distally on procursus (
Figs 323–325
) and genital bulb with distinctive prolateral distal apophysis and membranous distal elements (
Figs 326–328
).
